CSS (styles.css)
css
Copy code
/* Global Styles */
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    background-color: #f4f4f4;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
}

.container {
    width: 80%;
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 20px auto;
    background-color: white;
    padding: 20px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
}

header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
}

header h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 2.5em;
    color: #333;
}

header p {
    margin: 5px 0;
    color: #555;
}

section h2 {
    font-size: 1.8em;
    color: #333;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #4CAF50;
    padding-bottom: 5px;
}

section ul {
    list-style-type: none;
    padding: 0;
}

section ul li {
    margin: 8px 0;
    color: #555;
}

footer {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 20px;
    font-size: 1em;
    color: #888;
}

/* Styling for smaller screens */
@media (max-width: 600px) {
    .container {
        width: 90%;
    }
    header h1 {
        font-size: 2em;
    }
    section h2 {
        font-size: 1.6em;
    }
}
How to Use:
Save the HTML code into a file named index.html.
Save the CSS code into a file named styles.css.
Make sure both files are in the same folder.
Open index.html in a browser to view the resume.
Output:
The resume will display with the structure you've requested, featuring clean formatting and clear sections for personal details, objective, education, skills, hobbies, and more. The CSS styles ensure a neat, professional appearance with responsive design for smaller screens.




